---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import LegalNav from '../components/LegalNav.astro'
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro'

const EFFECTIVE_DATE = 'March 2, 2026'
const CONTACT_EMAIL = 'legal@absoluteear.com'
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — Absolute Ear"
  description="Terms of Service for the Absolute Ear app."
>
  <LegalNav pageTitle="Terms of Service" />

  <!-- ── CONTENT ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <main id="main-content" style="background:#f7f7f5; min-height:100dvh;">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-24">

      <p style="font-size:13px; color:#8d96a5; font-family:var(--font-mono); margin-bottom:1rem;">
        Effective {EFFECTIVE_DATE}
      </p>
      <h1 style="font-size:clamp(2rem,5vw,3rem); font-weight:700; letter-spacing:-0.03em; color:#0f1115; line-height:1.1; margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="lead">
        These Terms of Service govern your use of Absolute Ear, an ear training app for iOS and Android.
        Please read them carefully. By using the app you agree to be bound by these Terms.
      </p>

      <hr class="divider" />

      <section>
        <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By downloading, installing, or using Absolute Ear ("the App"), you agree to be bound by
          these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree to these Terms, do not use the App.
        </p>
        <p>
          These Terms constitute a legally binding agreement between you and the developer of
          Absolute Ear ("we," "us," or "our"). We reserve the right to update these Terms at any
          time. Continued use of the App after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of
          the revised Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Description of the App</h2>
        <p>
          Absolute Ear is an ear training application for iOS and Android that teaches musical note recognition,
          melodic dictation, and interval recognition through structured, progressive practice sessions.
        </p>

        <h3>Free Tier</h3>
        <p>
          Any five (5) course modules of your choosing are available at no charge and do not require
          account creation. Which modules are available depends on the curriculum dependency structure
          — you are not limited to a fixed sequence and may mix categories (for example, solo note
          modules alongside interval training). You may use guest mode to access these modules
          without signing in.
        </p>

        <h3>Premium Access</h3>
        <p>
          Modules beyond the five free modules require an active subscription, a one-time lifetime
          access purchase, or, for individual instrument packs, a one-time in-app purchase. See
          Section 5 for full details.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. Accounts</h2>

        <h3>Creating an Account</h3>
        <p>
          You may create an account using Sign in with Apple, Sign in with Google, or an email
          address with a one-time sign-in code. By doing so, you authorize us to receive your
          name and email address from the sign-in provider you choose (or Apple's relay email
          address if you choose to hide your email via Apple sign-in).
        </p>

        <h3>Guest Mode</h3>
        <p>
          You may use the free tier without creating an account. Progress made in guest mode is
          stored locally on your device and is not backed up to our servers. If you uninstall the
          App or clear your device data, guest mode progress cannot be recovered.
        </p>

        <h3>Account Responsibility</h3>
        <p>
          You are responsible for maintaining the security of your Apple ID. You are responsible
          for all activity that occurs under your account. Notify us immediately if you believe
          your account has been compromised.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Age Requirements</h2>
        <p>
          The App is not directed to children under the age of 13. By using the App, you represent
          that you are at least 13 years old. If you are under 18, you represent that a parent or
          legal guardian has reviewed and agreed to these Terms on your behalf.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Subscriptions and In-App Purchases</h2>

        <h3>Subscriptions</h3>
        <p>Premium access to the full course is available via auto-renewing subscriptions:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Monthly subscription</strong> — billed monthly</li>
          <li><strong>Annual subscription</strong> — billed once per year</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Subscriptions are managed and billed through the platform store you use to purchase:
          Apple's App Store (iOS) or Google Play (Android). Payment is charged to your store
          account at confirmation of purchase. Subscriptions automatically renew at the end of
          each period unless canceled at least 24 hours (Apple) or the day before (Google Play)
          the renewal date.
        </p>
        <p>
          You may manage or cancel your subscription at any time:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>iOS:</strong> iPhone Settings → Apple ID → Subscriptions</li>
          <li><strong>Android:</strong> Google Play app → Profile → Payments &amp; subscriptions → Subscriptions</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Canceling a subscription stops future renewals but does not entitle you to a refund for
          any current billing period.
        </p>

        <h3>Lifetime Access</h3>
        <p>
          Lifetime access to the full course is available as a one-time in-app purchase. This is a
          non-consumable purchase that permanently unlocks all current and future course modules for
          your store account (Apple ID or Google account), with no recurring charges. If you
          reinstall the App, you can restore this purchase at no charge using the in-app restore
          function.
        </p>

        <h3>Instrument Pack Purchases</h3>
        <p>
          Additional instrument sample packs are available as one-time in-app purchases. These are
          non-consumable purchases and are permanently available to your store account (Apple ID or
          Google account). If you reinstall the App, you can restore these purchases at no charge
          using the in-app restore function.
        </p>

        <h3>Pricing</h3>
        <p>
          Current pricing is displayed in the App at the time of purchase. We reserve the right to
          change subscription and purchase pricing at any time, with reasonable notice.
        </p>

        <h3>Refunds</h3>
        <p>
          All purchases are processed by the platform store (Apple or Google). Refund requests must
          be submitted directly to the store you purchased through:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>iOS (Apple):</strong> <a href="https://reportaproblem.apple.com">reportaproblem.apple.com</a></li>
          <li><strong>Android (Google Play):</strong> Submit a refund request via the Google Play app or Google Play Help</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We have no ability to issue refunds on behalf of Apple or Google.</p>

        <h3>Free Trial</h3>
        <p>
          If a free trial is offered, unused portions of a free trial are forfeited when a
          subscription is purchased. Trial availability and duration are displayed in the App at
          the time of offer.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Data Collection and Privacy</h2>

        <h3>What We Collect</h3>
        <p>When you create an account via Sign in with Apple, we receive:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your name (or the name you provide)</li>
          <li>Your email address or Apple's private relay email address</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We also store your practice data in the cloud, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Session history and accuracy statistics</li>
          <li>Per-note and per-unit performance data</li>
          <li>Streak and progress information</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This data is stored on servers provided by <strong>Convex</strong> (our cloud backend
          provider) and is associated with your account.
        </p>

        <h3>Local Storage</h3>
        <p>
          Whether or not you have an account, the App stores practice data locally on your device.
          This data remains on your device and is also synced to our servers if you are signed in.
        </p>

        <h3>Third-Party Services</h3>
        <p>
          The App uses the following third-party services which may collect data in accordance with
          their own privacy policies:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>RevenueCat</strong> — manages subscriptions and in-app purchases. RevenueCat
            may collect device identifiers and purchase history to manage entitlements and prevent
            fraud.
          </li>
          <li><strong>Convex</strong> — our cloud database and authentication provider.</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Apple</strong> — Sign in with Apple authentication and App Store payment
            processing (iOS).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Google</strong> — Sign in with Google authentication and Google Play payment
            processing (Android).
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Analytics and Crash Reporting</h3>
        <p>
          The App may collect anonymized usage data and crash reports to help us improve the
          product. This data does not identify you personally.
        </p>

        <h3>Your Rights</h3>
        <p>
          You may request deletion of your account and associated data by contacting us at the
          address in Section 14. Upon deletion, your cloud-stored practice data will be removed
          from our servers within 30 days.
        </p>
        <p>
          For full details, please review our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          All content in the App — including but not limited to audio samples, course content,
          graphics, the app interface, and underlying software — is owned by us or licensed to us
          and is protected by applicable copyright, trademark, and intellectual property laws.
        </p>
        <p>
          You are granted a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use the App for
          personal, non-commercial purposes in accordance with these Terms.
        </p>
        <p>You may not:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Copy, modify, or distribute any portion of the App</li>
          <li>Reverse engineer or attempt to extract the source code</li>
          <li>Use the App's audio samples outside of the App</li>
          <li>Resell or sublicense access to the App or its content</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>
          You agree to use the App only for its intended purpose of personal ear training and music
          education. You agree not to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to our servers or another user's account</li>
          <li>Use the App in any way that violates applicable law</li>
          <li>Interfere with or disrupt the App or servers connected to the App</li>
          <li>Use automated tools to scrape, crawl, or interact with the App</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p class="uppercase-legal">
          THE APP IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EITHER
          EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS
          FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT.
        </p>
        <p>We do not warrant that:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The App will be uninterrupted or error-free</li>
          <li>Any defects will be corrected</li>
          <li>The App or its servers are free of viruses or harmful components</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p class="uppercase-legal">
          TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, WE SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY
          INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, INCLUDING BUT NOT
          LIMITED TO LOSS OF DATA, LOSS OF PROFITS, OR LOSS OF GOODWILL, ARISING OUT OF OR IN
          CONNECTION WITH YOUR USE OF THE APP.
        </p>
        <p class="uppercase-legal">
          OUR TOTAL LIABILITY TO YOU FOR ANY CLAIMS ARISING UNDER THESE TERMS SHALL NOT EXCEED
          THE AMOUNT YOU PAID US IN THE TWELVE (12) MONTHS PRECEDING THE CLAIM.
        </p>
        <p>
          Some jurisdictions do not allow the exclusion of certain warranties or limitation of
          liability. In such jurisdictions, the above limitations apply to the extent permitted
          by law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>11. Governing Law and Disputes</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by the laws of the United States. Any disputes arising under
          these Terms shall be resolved in accordance with applicable United States law.
        </p>
        <p>
          You agree to resolve any dispute with us informally first by contacting us at the address
          below. If a dispute cannot be resolved informally, both parties agree to submit to binding
          arbitration in accordance with the rules of the American Arbitration Association, except
          that either party may seek injunctive relief in a court of competent jurisdiction.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>12. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. When we do, we will update the "Last
          Updated" date at the top of this page. If changes are material, we will provide notice
          within the App. Your continued use of the App after changes take effect constitutes your
          acceptance of the revised Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>13. Termination</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to suspend or terminate your account and access to the App at our
          discretion, including for violation of these Terms. Upon termination, your right to use
          the App ceases immediately. Sections 7, 9, 10, and 11 survive termination.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>14. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For questions about these Terms, account deletion requests, or other inquiries:
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <SiteFooter activePage="terms" />
</Layout>

<style>
  .lead {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #3d4451;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .divider {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid #e2e4e8;
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.1875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: #0f1115;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #0f1115;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #3d4451;
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  .uppercase-legal {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: #5a6270;
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #3d4451;
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }

  a {
    color: #0e9aa7;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
</style>
